commit.message: Release version 0.12.1

Test with PyPy3 in Travis CI

There's really no reason not to so let's have this covered. pypy3 is the
latest PyPy3 available in Travis.

Test with CPython 3.8 in Travis CI

This has been long forgotten.
Simplify CPython 3.7 Travis CI setup

Provide PEP 561-compatible type checking opt-in marker

This is in order for tools to pick up typing information while
analyzing client code.

Fix injecting request-scoped dependencies into teardown handlers

Closes GH-42.

Move the code to a package

This is necessary so that we can distribute the py.typed marker.
Don't install typing backport on recent Python versions
Add Coveralls coverage stats badge to the readme
